## Introduction to Streams API

- Main purpose is to perform some operation on collections.

- Parallel operations are easy to perform with stream API without having to spawn a multiple threads.

- Streams API can be also used with arrays or any kind of I/O


## Stream

- Stream is a sequence of elements which can be created out of a collection such as List of Arrays or any kind of I/O resources and etc...

List<String> names = Arrays.asList("Alataf", "Azad", "Warish");
names.stream(); // create a stream

- Stream operations can be performed either sequentially or parallel.
    names.parallelStream(); // creates a parallel stream